A man drowned in a small dam near Matlala road, Polokwane on Sunday. It is understood that the man believed to be in his twenties, was part of a church group. A bystander explained that the man disappeared under water and was nowhere to be found. The body was found later by the police divers. “Shortly before 10am paramedics from ER24 were called to the scene where they found police divers searching for man,” ER24 said in statement. Police are investigating the incident. -TNA REPORTER